- cs.SY (Systems and Control): Cellular automata can be seen as dynamical systems, and the paper deals with constructing a specific type of dynamical system.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): Cellular automata can be seen as models of computation, and the paper deals with constructing a specific type of computational model.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper deals with constructing a specific type of algorithm (a cellular automaton) that operates on a specific type of data structure (a grid in the hyperbolic 3D-space).
